# define function for desaturating colors
desat <- function(cols, sat=0.5) {
    X <- diag(c(1, sat, 1)) %*% rgb2hsv(col2rgb(cols))
    hsv(X[1,], X[2,], X[3,])
}

recons<-list()
path<-"/Users/lukas/sciebo/Projects/testing/tmp/dlcpar/output/"
file.names <- dir(path, pattern =".tsv")
for(i in 1:length(file.names)){
  recons[[i]] <- read.table(paste(path,file.names[i],sep=""),header=TRUE, sep="\t", stringsAsFactors=FALSE)
  recons[[i]]$relduploss<-(recons[[i]]$dup-recons[[i]]$loss)/recons[[i]]$dist
}
library(tidyverse)
names(recons)<-file.names
reconsAll<-recons[[1]]
for (i in 4:ncol(reconsAll)){
reconsAll[,i]<-rowSums(sapply(recons, `[[`, i), na.rm = TRUE)
}

reconsAll$duploss<-reconsAll$dup-reconsAll$loss
reconsAll$relduploss<-(reconsAll$dup-reconsAll$loss)/reconsAll$dist
